infos.default:
How to use <@1135411894262435881> :

</request s3:1178119204302491783> : requests a score from Splatoon 3 to be added to your score card. Please specify the stage, the rotation type (day only, green random, golden day only, etc.), your score, and attach proof in the form of a link to a message in <#747408376253775873>, or upload an image. Please use this command once for every score you want added.
**For Princess Scores:** select Princess as the rotation type, regardless of the actual rotation type. Similar commands exist for Splatoon 2, Splatoon 3 Big Run and Splatoon 3 Eggstra Work.

</profile s2s3:1178119204302491780> : displays a user's profile. Use the page option to view more detailed scores.

</import:1178119204302491781> : If you have scores from roles, this command imports them to your score card.
infos.request:
</request s3:1178119204302491783> : requests a score from Splatoon 3 to be added to your score card. Please specify the stage, the rotation type (day only, green random, golden day only, etc.), your score, and attach proof in the form of a link to a message in <#747408376253775873>, or upload an image link to a job on stat.ink, link to an image on the web, or upload a file. Please use this command once for every score you want added.
**For Princess Scores:** select Princess as the rotation type, regardless of the actual rotation type.
</request s2:1178119204302491783> : the same for s2.
</request bigrun:1178119204302491783> : the same for big run. No need to specify rotation type.
</request eggstra:1178119204302491783> : The same for eggstra work.
After your score request is approved/denied, you will receive a DM along with additional details.
A day-only score qualifies to be counted as a normal score (non-day-only) if you submit with the same proof, but users may choose not to do so.
infos.profile:
</profile s2s3:1178119204302491780> : displays a user's profile. Use the page option to view more detailed scores. 

</profile oss:1178119204302491780> can be used to see tournament finishes.
infos.import:
</import:1178119204302491781>
If you have scores from roles, this command imports them to your score card. this will only record the lowest possible score for that role, so please `/request` the exact score if you would like to.
infos.submit:
</submit:1322802982596771851>
Submit a score for One Shot Showdown. Include your score, @ mentions to all 3 of your teammates, and an attached screenshot of the shift from NSO.
infos.leaderboard:
</leaderboard:1322802982596771854>
Shows scores of all submissions for specified OSS or current OSS if none is specified. Unofficial leaderboard, as only the top 3 scores were verified.
infos.start:
For TOs.
</oss start:1357893918380916737>
Starts OSS with the specified code. The 15 minute timer will begin immediately, so please ensure you have announced the event already to give time for people to form teams.

You can also set the check option to true to check if the scenario is valid beforehand, without sending the start message.
infos.stop:
For TOs.
</oss stop:1357893918380916737>
Stops OSS after submissions are closed. Triggers the top 3 scores to be sent for approval, after which they will be announced.
infos.extend:
For TOs.
</oss extend:1357893918380916737>
Extends OSS by specified number in minutes.
infos.delete:
For TOs.
</oss delete:1357893918380916737>
 Deletes submission that includes the member that is @ mentioned. Sends a message to the submitter that their submission was deleted.
infos.leave:
</leave:1357893918380916739> 
Leave the OSS matchmaking queue. 
Note: this also removes any teammates you joined the queue with, if applicable.
infos.status:
</status:1387115839022563450> 
Check how many people are in the OSS matchmaking queue.

oss_messages.queueing:
will be starting in about an hour (see <#1344413960421511258> for specific time)! If you'd like to participate but need teammates, you have two options:
1. Use /join to join the matchmaking queue, along with teammates if you desire. If there are enough sign-ups, the system will automatically assign random teammates once the matchmaking queue closes, which happens 10 minutes before the tourney starts. Use /leave to remove yourself (and teammates, if any) from the matchmaking queue if necessary
2. Search for teammates yourself. You can use the regular LFG channels in OFS to do so, though please specify that you are pinging for OSS.
Note that all participants must be in this server. If you are not queueing, no sign-up is required.

See <#1330632117281095721> for more info.
<@&1330632674477473883>
oss_messages.captain: If you are a captain, please find an unused LFG channel and ping your 3 teammates.
oss_messages.awaiting:
**FOR ALL PARTICIPANTS**
To make everything streamlined:
- Designate someone as host, who also saves the scenario code
- Designate someone as the submitter; only one submission is accepted per team!
- Make sure everyone is either added as friends or in the correct pool
<@&1330632674477473883>
oss_messages.start:
- You must play the scenario **ONLY ONCE**! No backing out, or intentionally disconnecting to gain an unfair advantage. If you have a disconnection, we'll be running these events very often, so don't worry, just catch the next one!
- Please submit your score with the following format:
  - </submit:1322802982596771851>; attach proof by attaching an image of the shift from NSO, and @mention all your teammates.
  - You can submit in <#746130457455886337>, <#1330801952438878250>, or anywhere you can type as the submission will only be visible to you.

Good luck! <:OFS4a_goldenegg:737492285998104688>
<@&1330632674477473883>
